# Checkwright core-file manifest — gate-sdk/SPEC.md §check-core-files.
# One repo-relative path per line (`#` comments, blank lines ignored). The gate
# is red when a listed path is missing from the worktree or untracked. Retiring
# a surface deliberately means deleting its line in the same commit that removes
# the file — that manifest edit is the diff-visible intentional-removal valve.

# Iteration state machine + governance charter.
TASK-QUEUE.md
.workflow/WORKFLOW-STATE.txt
README.md
CLAUDE.md

# Public contribution surface: guide + GitHub-rendered issue/PR templates.
CONTRIBUTING.md
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/gate-defect.yml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml
.github/pull_request_template.md

# CI backstop: the workflow template + this repo's filled instance (§ci-backstop).
gate-sdk/templates/gates-workflow.yml
.github/workflows/gates.yml

# Live-site monitoring (not a gate): the scheduled deployment probe.
.github/workflows/site-health.yml

# Gate registry + graph rule content + the checked pre-commit/graph projections.
scripts/gates.list
scripts/gate-sdk-config.sh
scripts/graph-vocab.sh
scripts/identity.conf
scripts/git-hooks/pre-commit
docs/check-graph.html

# One SPEC.md per kit (each kit's canonical contract).
gate-sdk/SPEC.md
lifecycle-kit/SPEC.md
queue-kit/SPEC.md
canon-kit/SPEC.md
delegation-kit/SPEC.md
context-kit/SPEC.md
guard-kit/SPEC.md
drift-kit/SPEC.md
evidence-kit/SPEC.md

# Held-constant validate baseline + committed per-run evidence manifest.
.workflow/validate-baseline.txt
.workflow/validate-evidence.txt
